Package: metis
Type: Package
Title: MICOM Measurement Invariance and Multigroup Analysis for seminr PLS-SEM
Version: 0.3.0
Authors@R: person("Aaron", "Akuteye", email = "aaronakuteye@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A seminr-native implementation of the Measurement Invariance of
    Composite Models (MICOM) procedure of Henseler, Ringle and Sarstedt (2016)
    <doi:10.1108/IMR-09-2014-0304> for partial least squares structural
    equation modelling, together with thin wrappers for bootstrap PLS multigroup
    analysis and an optional permutation multigroup test. The MICOM Step 2
    compositional invariance statistic uses deterministic composite sign
    alignment and admissibility filtering of permutation re-estimations, and the
    output reports permutation admissibility explicitly. Results have been
    cross-verified against 'cSEM'::testMICOM across 54 datasets; 'cSEM' is used
    only for validation and is never a runtime dependency.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.1)
Imports: seminr, stats
Suggests: cSEM, testthat (>= 3.0.0), knitr, rmarkdown
VignetteBuilder: knitr
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
